==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Comestible
<hw>Co*mes"ti*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>comestible</ets>, fr. L. <ets>comesus</ets>, <ets>comestus</ets>,
p. p. of <ets>comedere</ets> to eat; <ets>com-</ets> + <ets>edere</ets>
to eat.]</ety> <def>Suitable to be eaten; eatable; esculent.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Some herbs are most <qex>comestible</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Sir T.
Elyot.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Comestible</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Comestible
<hw>Co*mes"ti*ble</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Something suitable to be
eaten; -- commonly in the plural.</def> <rj><au>Thackeray.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

